smooth scrolling-->
1.first search locomotive js github
2.then scroll down  goto usage and then css and click the link and then copy the entire code 
3.create another file loco.css and paste that code there.
4.now go back to usage and scroll down and goto smooth then copy ->
const scroll = new LocomotiveScroll({
    el: document.querySelector('[data-scroll-container]'),
    smooth: true
});
and make script.js file and paste the code there
5.instead of [data-scroll-container] change this to '#main' as our whole website is in main...

6.Now we want a locomotive script so now goto google and search locomotive js cdn then go to locomotive-scroll.min.js and copy the url and attach this to html file.
<!-- <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/locomotive-scroll@3.5.4/dist/locomotive-scroll.min.js"></script> -->


